description.narrative: By 2020, disadvantaged children, adolescents and families have improved their knowledge and attitudes on key behaviour and social norms/practices on integrated sector priorities, which contributes to Access To Justice, Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Cross-Sectoral Adolescent Development, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development (Covid), Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Harmful Practices (Fgm/C And Child Marriage), Hiv Prevention, Learning Outcomes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, adolescents, particularly girls, their families and communities adopt key healthy and protective behaviours and are engaged in the development process.
